# Use field 'Suorituksen_tyyppi' and create new DataFrame containing activities: 'Juoksu', 'Kävely', 'Pyöräily', 'Patikointi'

import pandas as pd

# Specify the path to my Excel file
excel_file_path = 'Activities2012-2022E.xlsx'

# Read the Excel file into a Pandas DataFrame
df = pd.read_excel(excel_file_path)

# Filter the DataFrame based on activities and distance criteria
selected_activities = ['Juoksu', 'Kävely', 'Pyöräily', 'Patikointi']
min_distance_threshold = 3

filtered_df = df[df['Suorituksen_tyyppi'].isin(selected_activities) & (df['Matka'] >= min_distance_threshold)]

# Display the filtered DataFrame
print("Filtered DataFrame:")
print(filtered_df.head())

# Calculate averages for each activity

import pandas as pd

# Assuming df is my original DataFrame
df['Aika'] = pd.to_timedelta(df['Aika'])

# Calculate averages for each activity
averages_df = df.groupby('Suorituksen_tyyppi').agg({
    'Matka': 'mean',
    'Aika': 'mean',
    
})

# Display the averages DataFrame
print("\nAverages for Each Activity:")
print(averages_df)

  • Remove column 'Otsikko' (and all the data in the column)

import pandas as pd

#  df_activities_filtered is the DataFrame loaded from the Excel file
excel_file_path = 'Activities2012-2022E.xlsx'
df_activities_filtered = pd.read_excel(excel_file_path)

# Remove specified columns
columns_to_remove = ['Kokonaisnousu', 'Paras_tahti', 'Keskitahti']
df_activities_removed_columns = df_activities_filtered.drop(columns=columns_to_remove)

# Create a new DataFrame containing columns in indexes from 0 to 9
df_subset = df_activities_removed_columns.iloc[:, 0:10]

# Show the shape and head of the DataFrame
print("Shape of the DataFrame with Columns Removed:")
print(df_subset.shape)

print("\nHead of the DataFrame with Columns Removed:")
print(df_subset.head())

Add new data¶
  • Add new variable in DataFrame for 'Hearbeat_variability' by calculating Maksimisyke - Keskisyke
  • Calculate 5 number summary (min, 25% value, median, 75% value, max) for it.
  • Find what activity has highest heartbeat variability?
In [39]:
# Add a new variable 'Hearbeat_variability' to the DataFrame
df_subset['Hearbeat_variability'] = df_subset['Maksimisyke'] - df_subset['Keskisyke']

# Calculate the 5-number summary
summary = df_subset['Hearbeat_variability'].describe()

# Display the summary
print("5-Number Summary for Heartbeat Variability:")
print(summary)

# Find the activity with the highest heartbeat variability
max_variability_activity = df_subset.loc[df_subset['Hearbeat_variability'].idxmax(), 'Suorituksen_tyyppi']

print("\nActivity with Highest Heartbeat Variability:", max_variability_activity)
